---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words With Double P — CAPPUCCINO, APPETITE, HIPPOPOTAMUS"
  description="Best double-P words for Scrabble. CAPPUCCINO (18pts), APPETITE (12pts), APPEASE (11pts). PP pattern strategy for premium square plays. Free word finder."
  keywords="scrabble double p words, cappuccino scrabble, appetite scrabble, pp words scrabble, double p strategy, double letter words, scrabble word lists"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Scrabble Words With Double P — CAPPUCCINO, APPETITE & More",
    "description": "Best double-P Scrabble words. PP pattern strategy for premium square plays.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-30",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-with-double-p" }
  })} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What are the best double-P words in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "CAPPUCCINO (18pts), APPETITE (12pts, bingo-eligible), and APPEASE (11pts). PP words pack 6 points from the P pair alone." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "How many P tiles are in a Scrabble bag?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Only 2 P tiles (3pts each). Drawing both is uncommon (~10% of games), making PP words a valuable surprise play." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Is CAPPUCCINO valid in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "CAPPUCCINO is valid in SOWPODS but at 10 letters it's too long for standard bingo. APPETITE and APPLIED are more practical PP bingo words." } }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words With Double P — CAPPUCCINO, APPETITE & More</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>4 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">With only 2 P tiles in the bag (each worth 3 points), drawing both is uncommon but rewarding. PP words pack 6 points from the P pair alone — add premium squares and scores skyrocket.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">18 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">CAPPUCCINO</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">12 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">APPETITE</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">11 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">APPEASE</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">2</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">P tiles in bag</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top Double-P Words</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top PP Bingo</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">APPETITE — 12 Points + 50 Bonus</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">A=1, P=3, P=3, E=1, T=1, I=1, T=1, E=1 · 8 letters</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">Both P tiles deliver 6 points. At bingo length, APPETITE scores 62 total from common letters around the PP core.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">☕ CAPPUCCINO</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">18 pts · 10 letters · PP + CC combo</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">📋 APPLIED</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">12 pts · 7 letters · PP + D=2 · Bingo</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🕊️ APPEASE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">11 pts · 7 letters · PP front-loaded</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🍎 APPLE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">9 pts · 5 letters · Quick PP play</p></div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">PP Pattern Strategy</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">PP usually starts words:</span> APPEAR, APPLIED, APPEASE, APPROVE — the APP- prefix dominates. When you hold both P's, scan for A+P+P openings first.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Use blank as second P:</span> A blank as P unlocks PP words without both real tiles. Worth it for bingo-length words like APPETITE (62 total).</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">HAPPY for quick points:</span> HAPPY (15pts) is strong with H=4 and Y=4. HIPPO (12pts) fits tight spots where longer PP words won't reach.</p></div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">HAPPY</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">15pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">APPEAR</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">HIPPO</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SUPPER</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Rarity Factor</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Only <span class="text-white font-medium">2 P tiles</span> exist (3pts each). Drawing both happens ~10% of games — when it does, you have exclusive access to PP words.</p>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-with-double-t/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words With Double T</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/best-words-with-double-letters/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best Words With Double Letters</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find double-P words from your tiles — free solver, no sign-up needed</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
